This paper discusses the ethical concerns related to the acquisition and analysis of human data for machine learning algorithms, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses factors such as auditability, benchmarking, confidence, data-reliance, and explainability, which are important considerations in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper emphasizes the need for responsible and representative data collection, which is relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories.
